            "description": "Climate Case Ireland was started by Friends of the Irish Environment and is the first case in Ireland to hold the government to account for its contributions to dangerous levels of climate change. On Friday, July the 31st, the Supreme Court quashed the government's 2017 National Mitigation Plan. Seven judges unanimously ruled that it did not give enough detail on the reduction of greenhouse gases.\nThe impact of the ruling is that the Government cannot make long-term commitments about climate change without showing how they would be achieved.\n\nAs a spokesperson for the case, I have spoken at several events including the Dublin Human Rights festival, Trinity College Green week, TU Dublin Activist Academy, DIT College Green week and more. I have also given a range of workshops and have organized climate awareness events for the case including 'Message to the Earth', in the Fumbally Stables, Dublin, and 'Dress to Protest' (for the climate rallies) in the Tara Building, Dublin. For more info, see: https://www.climatecaseireland.ie"
